<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><title>$ command line ruby cheat sheets</title><link charset="utf-8" href="/style.css" media="screen" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" /></head><body><div class="main"><div class="header"><h1><a href="/">cheat sheets.</a></h1><code class="header">$ command line ruby cheat sheets</code></div></div><div class="content"><pre>\e[1m   -   Change text to hicolor (bold) mode
\e[4m   -      &quot;    &quot;   &quot;  Underline
\e[5m   -      &quot;    &quot;   &quot;  Blink
\e[8m   -      &quot;    &quot;   &quot;  Hidden (same color as bg)
\e[30m  -      &quot;    &quot;   &quot;  Black
\e[31m  -      &quot;    &quot;   &quot;  Red
\e[32m  -      &quot;    &quot;   &quot;  Green
\e[33m  -      &quot;    &quot;   &quot;  Yellow
\e[34m  -      &quot;    &quot;   &quot;  Blue
\e[35m  -      &quot;    &quot;   &quot;  Magenta
\e[36m  -      &quot;    &quot;   &quot;  Cyan
\e[37m  -      &quot;    &quot;   &quot;  White
\e[40m  -   Change background to Black
\e[41m  -      &quot;       &quot;      &quot;  Red
\e[42m  -      &quot;       &quot;      &quot;  Green
\e[43m  -      &quot;       &quot;      &quot;  Yellow
\e[44m  -      &quot;       &quot;      &quot;  Blue
\e[45m  -      &quot;       &quot;      &quot;  Magenta
\e[46m  -      &quot;       &quot;      &quot;  Cyan
\e[47m  -      &quot;       &quot;      &quot;  White
\e[7m   -   Change to Black text on a White background
\e[0m   -   Turn off all attributes.

\e is the escape character, it will not work in single quoted strings (you'll get a literal '\e'). \033 can be used in it's place.</pre></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="footer">Powered by <a href="http://www.sinatrarb.com/">Sinatra</a>,
